Uses of Class
FibonacciNode

    • Uses of FibonacciNode in <Unnamed>

      Methods in <Unnamed> that return FibonacciNode 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static FibonacciNode MaxFibonacciHeap.addIntoList(FibonacciNode first, FibonacciNode second)
      This function merges two subtrees 'first' and 'second' in the root list and returns the max node If there is only one subtree,return it as the result.
      FibonacciNode MaxFibonacciHeap.insert(FibonacciNode node)
      This method inserts the node instance of FibonacciNode into the Fibonacci heap by creating a singleton tree and adding it to the doubly linked root list by calling addIntoList() function.maxNode pointer is updated with the maximum node in the new root list which is returned by the addIntoList() function.The total number of nodes in the tree (i.e heapSize) is incremented and the pointer to the maximum value is updated if necessary.
      FibonacciNode SpanList.nextFiboNode()
      returns next Fibonacci Node element in the list
      FibonacciNode MaxFibonacciHeap.removeMax()
      This function removes the maximum node pointed by the maxNode pointer.Here we remove the maxNode from the tree and reinsert the subtrees of the removed maxNode into the root level list.

      void MaxFibonacciHeap.increaseCount(FibonacciNode theNode, int newKey)
      This function increases the count of the node to newKey.If theNode is not a root and new key is more than the frequency of the parent key, remove subtree rooted at theNode from its doubly linked sibling list by calling the cut() function and inserting theNode into the root level list.
